50|$|The three-banded plover, or three-banded sandplover (<b>Charadrius</b> <b>tricollaris),</b> {{is a small}} wader. This plover is {{resident}} in much of eastern and southern Africa and Madagascar, mainly on inland rivers, pools, and lakes. Its nest is a bare scrape on shingle. This species is often seen as single individuals, but it will form small flocks. It hunts by sight for insects, worms and other invertebrates. Three-banded plovers have a sharp whistled weeet-weet call.|$|E

